org.opends.quicksetup

Class Installation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opends.quicksetup.Installation

  • public final class Installation
extends Object
    This class represents the physical state of an OpenDJ installation. All the operations are dependent upon the root directory that is specified in the constructor.

      • validateRootDirectory

        public static void validateRootDirectory(File rootDirectory)
                                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Performs validation on the specified file to make sure that it is an actual OpenDJ installation.
        Parameters:
        rootDirectory - File directory candidate
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if root directory does not appear to be an OpenDJ installation root. The thrown exception contains a localized message indicating the reason why rootDirectory is not a valid OpenDJ install root.
